cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on the structure and behavior of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training and performance of these networks, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the use of small images as datasets suggests a focus on computer vision, which would place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also touches on the interpretability of neural networks, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
